Hmmm, avoiding spoilers for AVR is going to be challenging Mostly came to say that I did two Cube drafts on MTGO this weekend. It was the first time in like three years I'd drafted on MTGO, and I had a fantastic time. Drafted a very solid W/b aggro deck the first time, and a bad B/w reanimator deck the second time. If it weren't for some misclicks (like giving my land protection from white instead of my creature with Eight-Tails), I'd have made the finals in the first. I correctly scrubbed out the second draft tl;dr Had fun, looking forward to the Cube returning. If you didn't catch it this time, you should next time.
Emkorial
Ars Legatus Legionis
Registered: May 11, 2000Posts: 33592
Posted: Mon Apr 09, 2012 9:16 am
Ufgt wrote:That timewalk card is insane. Shiiiiiit.it looks like a blast. I think the new Miracle Condemn card will be pretty bonkers to in EDH. Putting commanders on the bottom of libraries is sweet. Not happy with Giselbrand, if there is anything I've learned by building and playtesting and rebuilding my cube umpteen times is that lifelink is an EXTREMELY dangerous mechanic in limited. out of 400+ cards in my cube, precisely *1* has lifelink, and it's an enchanment (Armadillo Cloak). Given his CC, it probably won't matter since we won't be drafting him with unburial rites, but it still gives me the heebie jeevies to see big evasive lifelinkers. They've always been completely busted wide open in draft (Exaulted Angel, Sphinx of the Steel Wind, Chancellor of the Dross, etc)But I'm just really loving the Miracle mechanic in draft. I love the "Oh shit!" moments in MTG where you need to topdeck like a boss to suck out a game, and now they have an entire mechanic for it. I can see them being problematic in constructed. I mean, you could Top to keep sticking the new Time Walk 3rd card down, god forbid you hit a second one, to stack your turns up when you are that many turns away from comboing off. Overall I'm liking the set so far, but I've found a good limited environment usually rests on the backs of the uncommons, so we'll see what they all look like.
